header.gameNote: FRONTIER COMMUNICATIONS AMERICAN ATHLETIC CONFERENCE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - FINAL

videos.description: SMU's  Ben Emelogu heads to the locker room after running into a tough screen and falling to the floor.
videos.headline: SMU's Emelogu heads to locker room after running into tough screen

videos.description: SMU's Ben Moore throws down an ally-oop then later gets an offensive rebound and a finish through a foul.
videos.headline: SMU's Moore making presence felt in the paint

videos.description: Cincinnati's Troy Caupain breaks the all time assists record at Cincinnati with his mom in the stands.
videos.headline: Caupain breaks Cincinnati all time assists record

videos.description: Ben Emelegu hits a big 3-point shot as time expires in the 1st half.
videos.headline: Emelegu hits 1st half buzzer beater

videos.description: SMU head coach Tim Jankovich talks about his teams good 1st half performance and the physical strain of the toutnament.
videos.headline: Jankovich hopes his team has enough left in the tank

videos.description: Cincinnati head coach Mick Cronin talks about his teams need to clean it up offensively, and get out to fast start in the second half.
videos.headline: Cronin says bearcats need fast start in second half

videos.description: Semi Ojeleye knocks down the contested 3-point shot.
videos.headline: Mustangs 3-point shooting creating second half separation

videos.description: SMU head coach Tim Jankovich talks about his teams performance to win the American Athletic Conference tournament, and their talent in the NCAA tournament.
videos.headline: SMU's Jankovich talks about his teams great potential going into the tournament

videos.description: Semi Ojeleye is named the American Athletic Conference Tournament MVP.
videos.headline: Ojeleye wins AAC Tournament MVP

videos.description: Sterling Brown puts up 18 points and tournament MVP Semi Ojeleye adds 14 of his own to help No. 12 SMU to a 71-56 win over No. 15 Cincinnati in the AAC championship game.
videos.headline: SMU tops Cincinnati for AAC title
